1
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:09,720
Xiaoguang.

2
00:00:13,840 --> 00:00:14,640
Be careful.

3
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:16,440
If you're tired or hungry,

4
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:18,560
have a piece of candy.

5
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:27,040
I'll be waiting for you at home.

6
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:30,800
Wait for me to come back.

7
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:33,720
Go.

8
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:55,680
Guozhu,

9
00:00:55,720 --> 00:00:56,640
organize the files.

10
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,200
Zheng Bei, always follows the orders.

11
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:01,000
Don't act on your own.

12
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:01,720
Yes, sir.

13
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:02,880
Director Gao,

14
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:04,440
do you need a change of shoes?

15
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,320
These are starting to smell.

16
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,360
Have all the walkie-talkies been tested?

17
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:07,200
We're testing them now.

18
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,200
Director Gao?

19
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,160
Not now.

20
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,440
Guozhu,

21
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:16,120
if you want something to eat,

22
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:17,680
try one of these.

23
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:18,640
White Rabbit candy?

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:20,560
Forget it.

25
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:23,320
You're going on the mission. You eat it.

26
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:26,160
This is wedding candy, isn't it?

27
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:27,960
Don't be ridiculous.

28
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,880
Nothing's official yet.

29
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:31,280
In that case, I'm not eating any.

30
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:33,560
Here, Ran.

31
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:35,080
Keep them for yourself.

32
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,440
Here, Bei.

33
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:38,640
Keep them.

34
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,720
Let's go.

35
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,440
Bei, Ran, be careful.

36
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,000
Stay safe.

37
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,760
Yao, be careful.

38
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,640
Guozhu, help yourself to the candies!

39
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:57,420
[Executive Producer: Zhang Yimou]

40
00:03:21,940 --> 00:03:27,260
[The First Shot]

41
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:30,220
[Episode 30]

42
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,720
It's opening.

43
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,360
Don't push the door, Bei!

44
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:49,120
Done.

45
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,160
There's a bomb on the door.

46
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,160
Why didn't you radio us?

47
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:16,960
All clear.

48
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,560
The bomb's been defused.

49
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:22,480
It's all clear. Calm down.

50
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,040
That was a close one.

51
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,040
Good thing Uncle acted fast.

52
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:29,240
Bei, didn't you see
Liang Jiaju in there?

53
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,400
No one was there.

54
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,440
Didn't you say he was inside?

55
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,760
I saw him go in with my own eyes.

56
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:36,480
Right.

57
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,160
How did you two get out of that room?

58
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:40,520
There's a tunnel.

59
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,160
It leads straight
to the Drug Processing Factory.

60
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:45,160
So that guy must have
escaped through the tunnel.

61
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:45,960
No way.

62
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:46,920
There's only one way in and out.

63
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,040
We came through there

64
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,880
and didn't see anyone.

65
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:50,200
Officer Zheng,

66
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,160
we found a surveillance room over there.

67
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,320
I'll go take a look.

68
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,000
You keep an eye on the perimeter

69
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:57,000
and bring the PAP officers there
to clear out all the explosives.

70
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:57,640
Got it.

71
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,480
Come on, Uncle.

72
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,240
Nah, I won't be of help anyway.

73
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,760
Head back to the office
once you're done here.

74
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:06,240
I'll go back first
and cook something for you all.

75
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,000
Alright.

76
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,200
Little brat.

77
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,160
He burned all the important stuff.

78
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,480
We'll need the tech team to come in

79
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,040
and see if they can recover anything.

80
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,920
He's got all the surveillance footage

81
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,400
from the drug manufacturing
and processing factories here.

82
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,520
That must've been his hideout.

83
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:33,760
Xiaoguang,

84
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,040
see if you can find

85
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,560
a blueprint of this place.

86
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:38,800
Got it.

87
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,320
Where's this guy going?

88
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,880
Mao, look behind you.

89
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,720
Yeah, behind you.

90
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:09,520
A PAP officer just walked past

91
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:10,960
and is heading outside.

92
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,360
See what's up with him.

93
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:14,880
Officer!

94
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:16,440
Is your leg okay?

95
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:17,840
Stop right there!

96
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,760
Liang Jiaju's at Exit 3! Hurry!

97
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:25,440
Come on!

98
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:37,660
[One minute ago]

99
00:06:37,660 --> 00:06:39,340
[Two minutes ago]

100
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:41,060
[Three minutes ago]

101
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:43,800
[Eighty minutes ago]

102
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,920
This round's over.

103
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:49,520
You find a new place and start over.

104
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:20,060
[Forty-five minutes ago]

105
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:25,280
Go.

106
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:27,760
Go.

107
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,560
Liang Jiaju's definitely inside.

108
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,040
[Thirty-two minutes ago]

109
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:06,880
It's a thick door.

110
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,520
We can't pry it open.

111
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,400
Xiaoguang, do you have any explosives?

112
00:08:26,580 --> 00:08:30,620
[Eight minutes ago]

113
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:50,560
Officer,

114
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,720
is your leg alright?

115
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,520
Do you need someone
to bandage it for you?

116
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:14,180
[Five minutes ago]

117
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:34,100
[Three minutes ago]

118
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,560
Mao,

119
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:49,680
look behind you.

120
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,680
A PAP officer just walked past.

121
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,280
See what's up with him.

122
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:56,880
Officer!

123
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,160
Is your leg okay?

124
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:00,680
Stop right there!

125
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,720
Mao, hang in there!

126
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,280
Mao!

127
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,360
- Mao!
- Mao!

128
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,000
- Captain Zheng!
- I'm fine.

129
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,040
Go... Go after him.

130
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,440
He went that way.

131
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,040
Okay.

132
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,920
Hurry. Carry him out
and get him to the hospital!

133
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,200
Hurry up!

134
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:28,600
Give me a hand. Come on!

135
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:29,760
Be careful!

136
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:32,960
Just north of this factory

137
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,280
is a lumberyard,

138
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,400
Hongqi Lumberyard.

139
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:36,920
After that, it's Hongqi Road,

140
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,760
and there's a lumberyard nearby.

141
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,680
If he planned his escape ahead of time,

142
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,680
he's definitely got a getaway car
near the lumberyard.

143
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,560
I'm worried he might
have someone waiting for him there.

144
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,120
Could it be Li Wenlong?

145
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,280
Li Wenlong got away?

146
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,400
Listen, Yao,

147
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,840
head straight

148
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,760
to Hongqi Road with Wang

149
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,080
and block the road.

150
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,200
He's running there.

151
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,680
You'll definitely
beat him to it by car. Go.

152
00:10:58,680 --> 00:10:59,360
Okay, got it.

153
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,040
Let's go.

154
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:00,840
I'm coming with you.

155
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,800
Bring the medical kit with you.

156
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,160
Mai!

157
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:57,840
Coming.

158
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:58,560
Let's go.

159
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,040
Man, the wind.

160
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:04,200
Sirs, with this wind,

161
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,240
where are you two going?

162
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,200
We're going to do some training.

163
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,320
In this weather?

164
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,600
The broadcast just said

165
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,000
the wind might blow houses down,
and you're still going?

166
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,400
Even if the wind's blowing knives,

167
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:16,080
it won't stop us
from practicing on the high bar.

168
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:18,680
By the way, I've heard the news.

169
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,000
Have you set a date yet?

170
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:22,960
What are you talking about?

171
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,200
That young man seems like a great match!

172
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:30,120
Oh, look at her.

173
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:41,320
Dad!

174
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,160
What's wrong?

175
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,440
Why are you pouting like that?

176
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:45,760
You could almost
hang a bottle on your lips!

177
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,920
Did Mom talk to Ms. Wei about me again?

178
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,840
Did you bump

179
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:53,280
into Uncle Mai just now?

180
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,840
So you're the one who told him?

181
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,640
I might've drank too much yesterday.

182
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:00,960
You're the worst!

183
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,560
No birthday present for you!

184
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,840
Come on, the wedding's bound
to happen sooner or later anyway!

185
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,840
Isn't Bei back yet?

186
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:13,880
Not yet.

187
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:18,280
What's wrong?

188
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,440
Why the long face?

189
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:23,880
It's all Dad's fault.

190
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,160
Now the whole neighborhood knows.

191
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:28,120
Knows what?

192
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:31,000
About Zhao Xiaoguang!

193
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:32,080
Mrs. Zheng,

194
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,560
when's the wedding happening?

195
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:35,200
I think the Spring Festival
would be perfect.

196
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,160
No way.

197
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,480
It'd be too cold.

198
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:39,800
I think the Waking of Insects
would be perfect.

199
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,680
Don't be ridiculous.

200
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,440
Mom...

201
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,400
The Waking of Insects is about bugs!

202
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:46,800
I say Grain Rain would be perfect!

203
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,640
You don't plan a wedding
based on solar terms.

204
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:51,400
- Then what is it based on?
- Base on the almanac.

205
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:53,120
The almanac, right?

206
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,360
You go by the almanac!

207
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,160
This wind is insane!

208
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:15,960
Zheng Bei!

209
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:18,880
There's blood here!

210
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:27,000
Keep chasing.

211
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:35,200
You're finally here.

212
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,880
My family needs me. I'm leaving now.

213
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:37,600
Go ahead.

214
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:13,400
♪Cursed by the spring breeze♪

215
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:20,160
♪My heart cursed by the spring breeze♪

216
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:06,360
What's wrong?

217
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,040
Got sand in my eyes.

218
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:09,280
What?

219
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,640
He's got sand in his eyes!

220
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:12,480
I'm fine. Let's go!

221
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:16,680
Bei!

222
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:17,480
Zheng Bei!

223
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,080
Bei!

224
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,080
Zheng Bei!

225
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:22,080
Are you alright?

226
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,040
Are you okay?

227
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,520
Feeling a bit lightheaded.

228
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,360
What?

229
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:28,600
He's been pushing himself all day.

230
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,080
He probably has low blood sugar.

231
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:31,800
Got anything to eat?

232
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:32,600
Yeah.

233
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,440
Here, Bei. One for each of us!

234
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,120
Give them all to him!

235
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:40,800
I'll take one.

236
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:41,800
Here, Ran!

237
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:46,760
Here, Bei!

238
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,240
Nan gave these to you, didn't she?

239
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:53,120
Nothing gets past you!

240
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,400
How are you feeling now? Better?

241
00:16:57,880 --> 00:16:58,320
Let's go!

242
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:02,040
Come on.

243
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:03,120
Let's go!

244
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,480
When we go back,

245
00:17:07,320 --> 00:17:10,040
Uncle will get you some
sweet and sour pork

246
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:11,280
to replenish the sugar.

247
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:13,840
Why did Uncle come today?

248
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,000
To blow up the door.

249
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:16,560
He was worried

250
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,280
and insisted on doing it himself.

251
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:20,360
He almost blew us all up!

252
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,080
Liang Jiaju

253
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,240
tried to get us in the same place
and blow us all up.

254
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:29,080
What a heartless scumbag!

255
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:31,440
I blame Uncle, too.

256
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,560
We told him not to come,

257
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,000
but he insisted on coming!

258
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,000
Xiaoguang!

259
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:16,240
♪Cursed by the spring breeze♪

260
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:22,720
♪My heart cursed by the spring breeze♪

261
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:28,480
♪Can't say it out loud♪

262
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:33,960
♪Let's part over a drink♪

263
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:41,560
♪Cold night rain♪

264
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:47,400
♪Raindrops scatter
onto the photograph♪

265
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,760
Xiaoguang!

266
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:56,560
Pull him inside!

267
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:59,120
♪Memorized, I stare♪

268
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:02,400
♪At that faded photograph of you♪

269
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:11,320
♪Your beauty is frozen in time♪

270
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:17,080
♪The icy picture holds your warmth♪

271
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:23,360
♪It feels like countless voices
are speaking♪

272
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:27,400
♪Too bad I can't understand them♪

273
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:36,000
♪Is the wine deepening its taste?♪

274
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:41,280
♪Or is my heart getting hollow?♪

275
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,360
Cover me!

276
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:43,920
Got it!

277
00:19:58,680 --> 00:19:59,560
Xiaoguang!

278
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:01,920
Hang in there, man!

279
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,120
Xiaoguang, hang in there.

280
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,240
Stay with me, Xiaoguang!

281
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,960
Where's the car?

282
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,360
Where's the car?!

283
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,840
I'll tell you!

284
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:59,720
At the lumberyard, next to the cabin.

285
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:24,400
Xiaoguang!

286
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,880
